adviseScripts.text: Sigh...
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: Ugh... Why are you staring at me?
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: Do you have a bad hangover?
Are you stressed out from work?
I see what you were thinking.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: ... Your guess was correct.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: If that answers all your questions, then go away. This hangover is killing me.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: You think I would be like this for something as simple as work?
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: This isn't the first time I've been overworked...
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: Ugh, just go away, I'm annoyed.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: I stay away from a sensitive Yulha.
These days, I can't help but nag Privaty whenever I see her.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: But if I keep doing it, I know she'll get upset...
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: *Sigh* What should I do?
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: Still, shouldn't you say what's on your mind?
It might be a good idea to nag a little less.
That's right. I should say what's on my mind, right?
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: After all, I'm the one who always cleans up her messes.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: Don't I deserve a little nag or two?
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: Right... I should try and hold it in. Sure.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: But I'm the one who's always running around cleaning up her messes!
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: And now I can't even nag?!
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: Ugh! So annoying!
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: I share many sighs with Yulha while talking about Privaty.
Admi worries too much.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: It might be a sign that she is mature...
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: But I don't think it's good for a kid to be so mature, anyway.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: Tell her to learn from Privaty how to act like a kid.
Give her a vacation and send her to the Outpost.
Why is everything you say such nonsense?
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: Admi is already looking down on Privaty these days.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: Do you think she will want to learn from Privaty?
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: That's a good idea. You're there, too...
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: Maybe you can help her relieve some of her stress.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: I will send her there soon.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: I worry about Admi with Yulha.
I heard that eating can make stress go away.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: So, what should I eat? Something sweet, or something spicy?
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: Sweet.
Spicy.
Hmph, I heard spicy food is better for relieving stress...
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: Still, you made a good choice.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: I can't eat spicy food, anyway.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: But I can't eat spicy food.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: Choose something else.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: I go back and forth about food choices with Yulha.
I have a favor. Could you try to reign in your Nikkes a little more?
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: Because of all the troubles you're causing on the surface and the Outpost, the amount of paperwork...!
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: *Sigh*
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: Okay. I'll be more controlling.
I'm sorry, but that is impossible.
Don't make promises you can't keep.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: I know very well you can't control all those Nikkes.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: Not by yourself, anyway.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: Oh, yeah? You're not up to the task?
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: ... Fine.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: You can't possibly control all those Nikkes by yourself.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: Admitting your shortcomings is better than making promises you can't keep, anyway.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: I discuss solutions about the Nikkes at the Outpost with Yulha.
Hey, Newbie.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: Do you have somewhere you want to go on your vacation?
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: You think I have time for a vacation?
I'll just rest in the Commander's Room.
You never think about it?
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: Well, I guess that's true.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: There's no such thing as a vacation for us...
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: You are going to use your golden vacation days being stuffed inside a room?
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: I didn't think you were so uselessly lazy.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: ... But I guess it's not bad, either.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: I imagine a nonexistent vacation with Yulha.
Newbie, did you ever consider working as a regular soldier for the Central Government?
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: Instead of being a Commander, I mean.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: I did.
I didn't.
Hm? You did?
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: That's an unexpected answer.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: Hm... If you worked below me, I could have bossed you around.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: What a pity.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: Right. I knew you would say that.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: You were born to do this job.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: I discuss the Central Government with Yulha.
Every day this horrible, conniving woman keeps getting in my way.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: How can I get rid of her?
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: Ask her, "Do you like me?"
Bite her.
No. I don't want to hear her answer.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: I might even throw up just trying to ask.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: Ugh, just thinking about it is making my stomach churn.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: Bite her? With my teeth?
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: ... That's not a bad idea.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: I make plans for getting rid of the conniving woman with Yulha.
Hey, Newbie.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: Have you ever realized...
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: If, one day, our superiors gave the order,
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: Triangle will execute you?
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: I know.
Can't I just pretend it's not true?
Then... you still spend your time counseling me?
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: I can't imagine a bigger sucker than you.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: You stupid fool.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: You can't afford to pretend.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: Someday, my bullet might just be the one that stops your heart.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: I spend some serious counseling time with Yulha.
What is your ideal type?
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: Do any of the Nikkes suit you?
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: Someone like you.
I don't think there are any among the Nikkes...
Y-you fool! What are you saying...?!
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: If you're joking, I won't let it slide!
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: None of the Nikkes?
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: What a fool. You have higher standards than expected.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: Or... Do you not like the Nikkes because they are not human...?
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: I argue with Yulha about ideal types.
I've heard that listening to white noise can help you concentrate.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: Do you think there's any truth to that?
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: For sure.
I think it's complete nonsense.
If you say so.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: I personally prefer to work in silence.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: If we ever end up sharing the same workspace, things might get uncomfortable.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: That's what I said!
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: You can concentrate much better in a quiet environment.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: It's good that this place is as serene as it is.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: Yulha and I spend some more time talking to each other.
Damn this insomnia... I feel like death warmed over.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: I've heard you can get so tired that you can't even fall asleep.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: What should I do in a situation like this?
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: I'll sing you a lullaby.
Get a prescription for some sleeping pills.
I'm not a baby!
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: That won't help me fall asleep!
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: ... Well, I guess it won't hurt to listen to it just once.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: Hmmm...
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: I don't think this is severe enough to warrant a hospital visit.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: But if you think I should, I'll drop by the doctor later.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: Yulha and I tried to come up with ways to help her fall asleep.
Hey...
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: Do... do you think ghosts really exist?
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: Yes, they do.
Of course they don't.
But... how do you know that?
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: You don't mean...
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: Have you encountered one before?!
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: Y-yeah, that's right!
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: There's no such thing as ghosts.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: I feel much better.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: Yulha and I end up spooking each other while we have our discussion.
Hmm...
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: Say something.
Don't do anything.
Argh! Why can't you keep your mouth shut for a second?!
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: Now I have to recalculate everything!
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: All done.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: Sorry to keep you waiting. It was something urgent.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: Yulha and I have a conversation about working.
I'm curious,
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: what kind of weather do you prefer?
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: A rainy day.
A sunny day.
I personally don't like rainy days.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: The sound of the raindrops always breaks my concentration.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: I prefer it to just be overcast.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: I'm a big fan of sunny weather too.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: I can concentrate better.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: But I don't enjoy the glare in my eyes.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: Yulha and I have a friendly debate about the weather.
Newbie,
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: is there anything you hope comes true this year?
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: World peace.
That you take it easy for a while.
Wow. That may be the most far-fetched thing I've heard yet.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: You need to get your head out of the clouds.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: You think you can just flip a switch and have world peace?
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: Ha, so your wish has something to do with me?
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: I hope for the same thing.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: However, if my workload is any indication, I don't see that wish coming true anytime soon.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: Yulha and I have a conversation about wishes.
I love to space out while I'm taking a shower.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: The only problem is that I can't stay there longer.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: What do you usually think about when you're in the shower?
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: Pssh, you think I have time to take a shower?
I don't think about anything.
Yikes. Seems you're going through a rough patch right now.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: So you're the same as me.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: The only time I can ever get outside of my head is when I'm in the shower.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: Yulha and I start talking about our favorite shampoos.
I'm sick of drinking coffee whenever I feel tired.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: I want to drink something new. Is there anything you can recommend?
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: An energy drink.
A vitamin drink.
Yeah, that could work...
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: All right, I'll try an energy drink today.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: Blech! Vitamin drinks taste awful.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: Even your taste buds aren't trustworthy.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: I'd rather just drink a different type of coffee.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: Yulha and I continue discussing the topic of drinks.
If you could ask me any questions,
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: what would you ask?
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: When do you find time to rest?
Do you enjoy your job?
Jeez... I'm stumped on the first question.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: To be honest, I'm not so sure myself.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: What's the big idea of asking me such a stupid question?
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: That's it. Question time's over.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: Great, now you made me even more stressed!
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: I am unable to ask Yulha any more questions.
Newbie, why am I so tired?
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: Because you've been working all day.
Because you haven't left the office yet.
Exactly right. I have to do it all over again tomorrow as well.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: They even asked me to work on the weekend.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: Can you believe it?
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: Let's get one thing straight.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: I would if I could.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: Understood?
adviseScripts.speaker: Yulha

adviseScripts.text: I have a conversation with Yulha about work.
